# THE AI RUNNING COACH KNOWLEDGE BASE
## Part 2: Exercise Physiology for Coaches

> **Document purpose:** Part 1 established *why* training works in principle (adaptation, overload, specificity, individualisation, recovery). Part 2 goes one level deeper: the actual physiological machinery those principles are acting on. Every workout in Part 4 and every zone in Part 3 exists to move one or more of these eight systems. If the AI engine can't explain *which* system a workout trains and *why* that system matters for the athlete's goal race, it shouldn't prescribe the workout. This chapter is what makes that explanation possible.

