## 10.0 Synthesis: Energy System Training Rules

This table is the practical bridge from physiology (this chapter) to the intensity zones (Part 3) and workout library (Part 4). It should be treated as the engine's lookup table for "which system does this serve, and how is it best trained."

| System | Primary Training Stimulus | Adaptation Timescale | Best-Suited Zone (Part 3 preview) | Primary Relevance By Event |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Aerobic capacity (central) | High volume, sustained over months–years | Slow (months) | Zone 1–2 (Easy/Long) | All events, especially Half/Marathon |
| Aerobic capacity (peripheral) | Volume + moderate intensity | Slow–moderate | Zone 1–3 | All events |
| Anaerobic system | Short, maximal efforts | Fast (2–4 weeks) but high-risk | Sprint/neuromuscular | Mainly ≤1500m; small dose for all |
| LT1 (aerobic threshold) | High volume of comfortable-but-purposeful running | Moderate | Zone 2 | All events |
| LT2 (lactate threshold) | Sustained efforts just below MLSS | Moderate-fast, highly trainable | Threshold zone | Especially 10K–Marathon |
| VO2 max | 3–8 min efforts at high intensity | Fast initially, plateaus early | VO2max zone | Especially 5K/10K |
| Running economy | Volume + strength training + fatigue-resistance work | Slow, multi-year | Cuts across all zones | All events |
| Fat oxidation | Chronic easy-pace volume | Slow | Zone 1–2 | Especially Half/Marathon |
| Glycogen utilisation/storage | Long runs + fueling practice | Moderate | Long run / race-pace work | Especially Half/Marathon |
| Muscle fibre recruitment/economy durability | Race-pace segments late in long efforts, year-round neuromuscular work | Slow, multi-year | Strides/hills + long run inclusions | All events |

